008, David Sanders wrote:<br />&gt;<br />&gt; I recently discovered that x86 kernels won't boot under Virtual PC.<br /><br />What CPU does Virtual PC emulate? As far as Wikipedia is concerned (not <br />that I'd take it on complete faith) it emulates a 32-bit Intel Pentium II.<br /><br />And that commit makes the kernel use the "P6 nops" for such hardware. <br />Maybe Virtual PC doesn't support the newer intel nop things?<br /><br />Intel docs say that it should be available on any intel CPU that has <br />CPUID.01H.EAX[11:8] = 0110B or 1111B. That's the "family ID", and Pentium <br />II should have a family ID of 6 (ie that 0110B case).<br /><br />So it sounds like a Virtual PC bug, but I dunno. And maybe we should just <br />use the legcay nops for anything that isn't modern (ie P4+ or Core)?<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
